item.title: I don't know what's my base
item.dc:creator: @X_Entinity_X X Entinity X
item.description:
@X_Entinity_X wrote:

[quote=“TOMSCAPE BETA, post:7, topic:376238”]You can usually tell by the layout of server files, and the variables each one uses. Deltascape commonly uses sM and sendMessage. I haven’t used Figmentscape in many years, but it isn’t a ‘base’ so to speak, PI also uses getPA().sendMessage or something like that (never used PI).

My point is you can tell based on the variables each server uses. As for differences, PI is packaged, is said to have better networking capabilities. Deltascape is just deltascape.
And Figmentscape is just…um…no idea.[/quote]

Sure, if your learning JAVA, learn something easyer, well not that Delta is easyer, just that it’s not packaged.

Deltascape is just deltascape.

LMFAO
